OL,3,CThousands of pieces of rubbish left on
OL,4,CWales' biggest mountain
OL,6,FThousands of pieces of rubbish have
OL,7,Fbeen collected by campaigners in just
OL,8,Fsix hours on Wales' biggest mountain.
OL,10,FMore than 2,700 pieces of litter were
OL,11,Fremoved from Yr Wyddfa including 800
OL,12,Fdrinks containers.
OL,14,FThe area had never previously been
OL,15,Flitter-picked, so it's thought some of
OL,16,Fthe rubbish could be 100 years old.
OL,18,FThe clean-up was carried out by
OL,19,Fvolunteers from the British
OL,20,FMountaineering Council (BMC), with
OL,21,Fsupport from Trash Free Trails.
